        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:34PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 434 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms near Billings.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Billings, Laurel, Lockwood, Billings Heights, Billings West End,
Huntley, Acton and Crow Indian Reservation.

Strong winds may occur with little to no rain present.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
